ACT:
 Bihar Control of Crimes Act 1981-Section 12 read with section 2 (d). For preventive detention under section 12 authorities must be satisfied that the person to be detained is anti-social element as defined in section 1(d).
 Bihar Control of Crimes Act, 1981-Section 2 (d)- Definition of 'antisocial element'-Interpretation of expression 'habitually' in sub-clause (i), (ii) and (iv)- Meaning of.
 Interpretation of statutes-Rule of-Law of preventive detention must be strictly construed.
 Practice-When person enlarged on bail by competent criminal court, great caution should be exercised in scrutinising validity of preventive detention order which is based on the very same charge which is to be tried by criminal court.
 Words and Phrases-Expression `habitually'-Meaning of.
 
